  "1 - x^2/2! + x^4/4! - ...": "",
  "sin(x) = x - x^3/3! + x^5/5! - x^7/7! + ... = sum of (-1)^n x^(2n+1)/(2n+1)! for n=0,1,2,.... This contains only odd powers of x, reflecting that sine is an odd function.": "",
  "What is the relationship between derivatives and rates of change in trig applications?": "",
