  "A ladder 10 ft long leans against a wall. The bottom slides away at 2 ft/s. When the bottom is 6 ft from the wall, how fast is the angle between the ladder and the ground decreasing? (Use cos(theta) = x/10)": "",
  "d(theta)/dt = -2/5 rad/s": "",
  "d(theta)/dt = -1/3 rad/s": "",
  "d(theta)/dt = -1/8 rad/s": "",
  "d(theta)/dt = -1/4 rad/s": "",
  "cos(theta) = x/10. Differentiating: -sin(theta) d(theta)/dt = (1/10) dx/dt. When x = 6: sin(theta) = 8/10 = 4/5. So -(4/5) d(theta)/dt = (1/10)(2) = 1/5. d(theta)/dt = -(1/5)/(4/5) = -1/4 rad/s.": "",
  "An engineer models temperature as T(t) = 20 + 15sin(pi*t/12) degrees C, where t is hours since midnight. At what rate is temperature changing at t = 6 (6 AM)?": "",
